    "_comment": "Self-contained CMS-in-CMS example (issue #30). Recreates a Team Members app: a public list/detail pair (/team-members + /team-members/{record_id}) for visitors, plus a CMS-in-CMS admin trio (a /cms/team-members/form append form that OWNS the data table, a /cms/team-members list with inline delete, and a /cms/team-members/{record_id} detail). The entry styles do NOT hardcode a table name: they reference the owning form section with the portable token \"table\":\"@section:team-members-form\", which the importer relinks to the new form section id. The bundle's data_tables[] block carries the column names plus sample rows keyed by human field name; import with options.importData=true to seed them. Content fields use the default-install locales de-CH and en-GB; if your install lacks one, import fails naming the missing locale. If /team-members is taken, set a keyword + route prefix in the import dialog. Import via Admin > Pages > Import. NOT auto-seeded.",
